First Lady Melania Trump and Under Secretary of State for Political Affairs Thomas A. Shannon will present the 2017 Secretary of State's International Women of Courage (IWOC) Award. The award ceremony, now in its 11th year, honors women who have demonstrated exceptional courage, strength, and leadership in improving their communities. Over 100 courageous women from more than 60 countries have been honored by the IWOC. The ceremony aims to showcase and support these women who have put their personal safety and lives at risk. Melania Trump expressed her honor in sharing the stage with these women, emphasizing the importance of women standing together and working towards gender empowerment and respect for people from all backgrounds. The winners of the IWOC award will be announced by the State Department and the event will be livestreamed on the Department of State's website. The hashtag #WomenOfCourage can be used for news and social media updates about the award.